org.vesselonline.test
Class WebSite

java.lang.Object
  org.vesselonline.test.WebSite

public class WebSite
extends java.lang.Object

Represents a web site, or a set of connected HTML resources. Contains the frames, HTTP session, and resources that make up the site, along with supporting information about the associated test suite.

Version:
1.0
Author:
Steven Handy
See Also:
WebSession, WebResource, XmlUtils

WebSite

public WebSite(java.lang.String xmlSiteFile)
        throws javax.xml.parsers.ParserConfigurationException,
               javax.xml.xpath.XPathExpressionException,
               org.xml.sax.SAXException,
               java.io.IOException
Constructor builds the web site and associated WebSession and WebResource objects that comprise the site. A well-formed jWebUnitSiteDescription XML file is required.
 
This constructor makes heavy use of the XPath expression processing provided by the XmlUtils object created for this site instance.

Parameters:
xmlSiteFile -
Throws:
javax.xml.parsers.ParserConfigurationException
javax.xml.xpath.XPathExpressionException

getFrames

public java.util.Set<java.util.Map.Entry<java.lang.String,java.lang.String>> getFrames()
Gets the set of frames that may exist in the HTML structure for this web site.

Returns:
Set of Map.Entry objects containing information about frames identified for this web site. The format of the entry is key=name, value=test fixture for the frame.

getFrameFixture

public java.lang.String getFrameFixture(java.lang.String frName)
Gets the test fixture that is defined for the frame. The test case within that fixture will have the same name as the frame. That test case is used to define elements that should always be present for that frame, regardless of the resource being displayed.

Parameters:
frName - Name of the frame for which to obtain the test fixture.
Returns:
Name of the test fixture for the specified frame.
